The paper deals with the problem of finding maximum weight perfect $f$-factors in general graphs, which involves graph algorithms and combinatorial optimization. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are all likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper presents a new algorithm with improved running time, which involves computational complexity and information theory, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory) also possible sub-categories.
